node.text: This Plum Galette from Chef Jacques Pépin is a rustic tart with an elegant finish. The buttery, flaky pâte brisée dough gets filled with fresh, seasonal fruit and baked until richly browned in the oven. A final brushing of fruit preserves provides flavorful and beautiful sheen. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.text: The inspiration for this Spicy Tofu and Zucchini Stew that @annie.h.shi makes for cozy weeknight dinners every season of the year comes from Soondubu Jjigae, a spicy Korean tofu stew, that she grew up eating at restaurants. The recipe features an umami-rich broth powered by dashi packets, gochugaru, doenjang (fermented soybean paste), and gochujang. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.text: “I think this cookie is so elegant and so New York chic and I’m gonna take it to SoHo,” says Chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) as she adds gold leaf to her take on the classic Black and White cookie. Bling aside, these Black and Ruby Cookies are already extra special with ruby chocolate instead of white, buttermilk instead of whole, and rye flour as a nod to iconic NYC deli breads. Find out how to make them by visiting this link:https://bit.ly/3zD88fk or tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.title: Pastries with Paola | Black and Ruby Cookies

Tap the link in bio for this a-maize-ing recipe!

Summer may be on its way out, but there are still plenty of good grilling days ahead. From chicken skewers to Caesar salad, we rounded up 15 grilled dishes everyone should know how to make, according to chefs, so you'll be on summer mode all year long.  Tap the link in bio for the best grilled recipes to add to your repertoire. 
📸: @protazio

node.text: Instead of fermenting for days or weeks at a time, this Quick Cucumber Kimchi is ready in two hours. Crisp vegetables and a spicy marinade of gochugaru, garlic, ginger and fish sauce come together to create this favorite Korean condiment that instantly boosts any meal. Tap the link in bio for the recipe! Recipe🥒: Bill Kim Photo: @johnkernick

These finger-lickin' wings deserve an invite to the cookout. Cherry preserves with habanero chile create a fabulously sticky, sweet, and spicy lacquer for these Smokin' Sweet Chicken Wings with Cherry Barbecue Glaze. Tap the link in bio for the recipe! 
Recipe🍗: @recipegoddess 📸: @lucyschaeffer

node.text: This Roasted Broccoli Steaks with Tomato Butter and Tapenade recipe is a plant-based stunner! Treat the cruciferous veggie like a steak by roasting thick slices of it to achieve a lightly charred crust. Then turn up the flavor with an umami-packed quick sauce enriched with just the right amount of butter. Tap the link in bio for the recipe! Recipe🥦: @vernickphilly 📸: @dmalosh

node.text:
The abundance of figs required for this recipe leaves the decoration and texture of this dense and fudgy Chocolate and Fig Cake up to interpretation.  Choose sweet Mission figs or juicy, velvety Brown Turkey figs for for different, but equally amazing results. Break out the mixer and tap the link in bio for the recipe!
Recipe🍰: Yossy Arefi 📸: @caitbensel

Chill out with this Tangy Cucumber Soup recipe from @justinchapple. Yogurt, lemon juice, and garlic get blended into this no-cook soup that can double as a dip for for crudité, dressing for a salad or sauce for grilled meat. Tap the link in bio for the recipe! 
📸: @conpoulos_photographer

node.text:
Cooking steak is a paradoxically delicate matter for a powerfully primal affair which is why it wouldn't be a surprise if you're making a mistake here or there. Lucky for you we compiled a list of 11 mistakes to avoid when grilling steak, according to chefs. Tap the link in bio for the ultimate crash course in how—and how not—to cook steak! 
📸: @gettyimages

node.text:
It's time to light up the grill for this Double-Cut Rib Eye with Sweet Gorgonzola Butter recipe. The juicy combo of indulgent Gorgonzola compound butter and marbled beef alongside fresh heirloom tomatoes is perfect for entertaining during the summer holiday weekend and so good you'll want to pass the bones around the table at the end of the meal. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe! 
Recipe🥩: @suzannetracht 📸: @protazio

node.text: This gorgeous Grilled Summer Squash with Blue Cheese and Pecans is an excellent choice for late summer BBQs and picnics. @chefandthef suggests slicing squash lengthwise into quarters and then removing the seedy interior for a uniformly crisp texture. Tossed with a bright, lemony dressing this side dish is a keeper. Tap the link in bio for the recipe! 📸: @evakolenko

node.text: This Plum Galette from Chef Jacques Pépin is a rustic tart with an elegant finish. The buttery, flaky pâte brisée dough gets filled with fresh, seasonal fruit and baked until richly browned in the oven. A final brushing of fruit preserves provides flavorful and beautiful sheen. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!
